		   <tr><td class="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform" valign="top" id="forumSubject">Question About Guild Recruiting<br clear="all" /><script type="text/javascript">document.title = document.title + ": Thread: Question About Guild Recruiting";</script>
		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Thu, Mar 31st 5:36 PM2005 </span><span class="notbold">| <span class="sm">IP: Logged</span> | <a href="/forum.html?forum=1&mid=1112308554113348520&post=1"><a class="sm" href="/forum.html?forum=1&mid=1112308554113348520&num=11&page=0&post=1&replyto=1112308554113348520"><img src="/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif" border="0" alt="Reply..." height="11" width="17" /> Reply to this</a></a> | <a class="sm" href="/db/journal2.html?user=432754"><img border="0" src="/shared/user_journal.gif" border="0" height="12" width="17" /> User's Journal</a>   <a name=1112308554113348520></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform" ><span class="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=432754"><span id="Scholar">martenp</span></a><b><span id="Scholar"><br>Scholar</span></b><br /><img alt="Avatar" height="99" width="91" src="/uf/martenp/bardmart.JPG"><br /><br /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><br />124 posts
		   <br /><nobr><span class="notbold">Score</span>: Decent [3.07]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=martenp&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%">
<p>Ok, I know there are several methods to go about getting new guildies.&nbsp;&nbsp; <br /> <br />Shouting in PoK: while effective as far as advertising goes, seems a bit irritating and spamish. <br /> <br />Guild website:  Eh, don't like having to go outside the game to do stuff. <br /> <br />Guild Hall posting boards: my real question I suppose, anyone having luck with this new feature?   <br /> <br />Any other suggestions for getting a few good guildies to our family-type guild?  How rude is it to ask people who are already in a guild if they like their guild and want to switch?   <br /> <br /> <br /></p>
<br /><span class="sm">----------------------------</span><br />Mar'ten  <br />Level 49 bard AR - Temple Draconis <br />Level 45 bard FV - Mortal Ascension <br />Level 17 bard AB - Unguilded <br />(along with assorted alts)  <br /></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8"></td><td align="right" id="fs8" >11 Replies</td></tr></table>
</td></tr></table></td></tr><tr><td>

		   <table class="mform2"  border="0" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="0" width="100%" >
		   <tr><td class="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform2" valign="top" id="forumSubject">
		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Thu, Mar 31st 5:51 PM2005 </span><span class="notbold">| <span class="sm">IP: Logged</span> | <a class="sm" href="/forum.html?forum=1&mid=1112308554113348520&num=11&page=0&post=1&replyto=1112309442337462316"><img src="/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif" border="0" alt="Reply..." height="11" width="17" /> Reply to this</a></a> | <a class="sm" href="/db/journal2.html?user=340246"><img border="0" src="/shared/user_journal.gif" border="0" height="12" width="17" /> User's Journal</a> | <a class=sm href="mailto:TheMightyMagnu@allakhazam.com"><img src="/shared/mail3.gif" border="0" height="10" width="17" /> Email User</a>  <a name=1112309442337462316></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform2" ><span class="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=340246"><span id="Scholar">TheMightyMagnu</span></a><b><span id="Scholar"><br>Scholar</span></b><br /><img alt="Avatar" height="60" width="60" src="/uf/TheMightyMagnu/C._Montgomery_Burns.jpg"><br /><br /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><br />351 posts
		   <br /><nobr><span class="notbold">Score</span>: Decent [2.98]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=TheMightyMagnu&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%">
<p>K I believe I can help with this. <br /> <br />1: This has netted me a bunch of guild members, although they tend to be a little fluttery. By that I mean they don't stay around for long. For a new guild, what really counts is number, as you want to have over ten members at all times. Once you have ten solid members, then you should try to recruit friends and people who you think would be more loyal. <br /> <br />2: I don't have a website, as it is still a really small guild <br /> <br />3: I don't have DoN so I can't comment <img border="0" src="/shared/smilies/cry.gif" alt="icon"/> <br /> <br /> <br />Misc: <br /> <br />Overall, people don't like it if you're pushy. If someone is in a guild and wants to leave, don't ask them to join you, but casually mention that you are leader (or officer, as it were) of the guild. Then they are more likely to remember you. <br />Also, people you've made a good group with are more likely to be loyal and stick with you than the PoK thing. <br /> <br />Another thing: While this is a little obvious and purely opinionated, GET A GOOD NAME FOR YOUR GUILD heheh...a lot of people have joined my guild because it has a cool name. It sounds cheesy but it works in your favor.\ <br /> <br />Hope this helps <br /> <br /> <br /> <br /></p>
