		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform" ><span class="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=276178"><span id="Scholar">Dothammer</span></a><b><span id="Scholar"><br>Scholar</span></b><br /><img alt="Avatar" height="89" width="47" src="/uf/Dothammer/simp_hom.gif"><br /><br /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*"/><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><br />1142 posts
		   <br /><nobr><span class="notbold">Score</span>: Decent [3.33]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Dothammer&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%">
<p>Just my OPINION... <br /> <br />Shouting in PoK or elsewhere: Tacky.&nbsp;&nbsp;Never investigated any guild who did this. (Ok you got me, I'm a snob.) <br /> <br />Message Board in-game: Have not used it to recruit, no opinion yet.  Seems like this could be a good way to advertise your guild. Not sure if it is better than shouting in PoK but it is less tacky.  People who see you would have actually had to make the effort to check the board.  Might have to wait until this is the 'norm' I guess. <br /> <br />Hang around newbie areas and send blind tells to people who have good equipment but are not tagged:  I have seen this done.  Stealth recruiting? <br /> <br />I would not try to recruit someone who is already in a guild.  Just seems underhanded. We have a rule in our guilds' recruitment procedure prohibiting this. <br /> <br />Our 'family' type guild tries to recruit well behaved players who want to advance and learn about the game.  The best additions to our guild have come from grouping with good players, having them check out our website and get to know if they like our guild.  Big part of our guild IS members checking info sites and posting ideas and what-not.   <br /> <br />If you want a bunch of members fast, this is not the way to do it, naturally.  I am guessing with the sever merges this will be a good time to pick up new members. <br /> <br />Edit: Just like to add that I have seen guilds offering buffs in PoK with the express tag: Free to XX guild members.  Do they think people will thinK: Hey, if I join this guild I can get free buffs all the time...Tacky...Maybe our guild is small because I know I can get free buffs from them just about anytime I need them. <br /> <br /><i><span class="sm">Edited, Thu Mar 31 18:07:34 2005 by Dothammer</span></i></p>
