		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform" ><span class="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=247125"><span id="Scholar">Jiggidyjay of the Seven Seas</span></a><b><span id="Scholar"><br>Scholar</span></b><br /><img alt="Avatar" height="98" width="77" src="/uf/Jiggidyjay/ava4.jpg"><br /><br /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*"/><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><br />1906 posts
		   <br /><nobr><span class="notbold">Score</span>: Good [3.52]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Jiggidyjay&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%">
<p>/ooc and /shout is definately tacky. Don't do it. <br /> <br />Blind tells is tacky also. When my bard was between guilds, about level 64-65, I was CONSTANTLY getting tells. One time I zoned into Plane of Tranquility and immediately ran straight to BoT. I had 2 tells before I even reached BoT. That's crazy. I never took any of those tells seriously. The way I saw it, if they were so willing to bring me in, someone they didn't know from a hole in the ground, the guild must not be very picky, and well, I want a guild that's at least somewhat picky. I had a guild or two that was hounding me also. As soon as they saw /lfg on my name, I'd get an invite, then they'd talk about how much they'd love to have me in their guild, so on and so forth, the whole time we were hunting. They were alright people, and I actually knew most of them (including the GL) from a prior guild alliance, but again, I wasn't really interested. <br /> <br />One of the family guilds I was in a long time ago used to do aid stations every few weeks. Basically, you set up in a high traffic newbie/lowbie hunting area and just offer free buffs/heals/train derailments/etc. You don't even have to ask anyone if they want to join your guild, because a lot of them will think &quot;Wow, what a cool guild&quot; and ask you if they can join. Again, this isn't a very selective process though. If you have an application process though, this is a way to at least get people interested and in the pipe.</p>
<br /><span class="sm">----------------------------</span><br /><a href="HTTP://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1006062&resize=true" title="HTTP://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1006062&resize=true" target="akztarg">Jiggidyjay</a> - <span class="sm">Mr Ranger</span> <br /><a href="HTTP://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1003866&resize=true" title="HTTP://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1003866&resize=true" target="akztarg">Zingin Ansinging</a> - <span class="sm">Mr Bard of <a href="HTTP://firestormers.com/viewnews.php" title="HTTP://firestormers.com/viewnews.php" target="akztarg">The Firestormers</a></span> <br /><a href="HTTP://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1006061&resize=true" title="HTTP://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1006061&resize=true" target="akztarg">Zolotaya</a> - <span class="sm">Ms Necro</span> <br />- <br /><a href="HTTP://bf2tracker.com/bf2_userprofile.php?bf2id=44675760" title="HTTP://bf2tracker.com/bf2_userprofile.php?bf2id=44675760" target="akztarg">Zingin</a> - BF 2</td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8">Posting from over the river and through the woods...</td></tr></table>
