<p>Wow, really great suggestions, thanks for taking the time.&nbsp;&nbsp; <br /> <br />You guys echo my own feelings about what I've seen done in the past.  I didn't care for the idea of luring people away from their guilds, as stated, it seems sneaky and underhanded.  <br /> <br />We're not looking for uber numbers, so long as we've got a good core, I'll be happy.  I'm content to find people just by grouping with them. <br /> <br />I think it's more important that we all get along and have fun, and I want everyone in the guild to be able to feel that's the point.  So I guess that's our &quot;mission statement&quot;  If our guild has a name for ourselves for being good, friendly players, then we should have no trouble finding allies to hunt with and raid with when we get to be big bards and pallies and shammies.  </p>
