		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform2" ><span class="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=103091"><span id="Scholar">dbernor</span></a><b><span id="Scholar"><br>Scholar</span></b><br /><img alt="Avatar" height="100" width="100" src="/uf/dbernor/d1.jpg"><br /><br /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><br />463 posts
		   <br /><nobr><span class="notbold">Score</span>: Good [4.09]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=dbernor&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%">
<p>Here's my <img border="0" src="/shared/smilies/twocents.gif" alt="icon"/> <br /> <br /> <br />When I started my guild and got up to about 20 toons or so, I was worried that they would get bored and start leaving. <br />I had just upgraded one of my earrings and the one I replaced had some nice stats on it and was usable by everyone. So I thought I'd do a guild event...Hide and Seek. <br /> <br />Firts person to find me in POK won the ring. (No tracking was allowed) Off I went and the whole hunt took about 20 mins. A mid 20's Beastlord found me and was thrilled to get the earring. <br />Then other members started putting up plat or items and we had a blast for almost 2 hours. And I do mean a BLAST! <br /> <br />Why am I telling you this? <br /> <br />Because it turned out to be an inadvertant membership drive!  <br />People were seeing my guild members running all around POK for 2 hours! They would send em tells like &quot;what are you doing?&quot; and My&nbsp;&nbsp;guildies would tell em, next thing I knew I would be doing on the spot interviews for invites. <br /> <br />Give it a shot, it was a win/win event. Guild had fun and we got a bunch of new members. (Knock on wood all but 4 are still active in guild!) <br /> <br />We've done 2 more similar events in POK and both of those have netted us new members as well.</p>
